ha

content.detailedDescription:
Ufo sighting in littleton, massachusetts, nov. 1, 2015 - 5:15 pm est

... did anyone else see the really up-close ufo this evening at 5:15 pm est over littleton, massachusetts by the groton / littleton route 119 exit off interstate highway route 495 (which runs north / south) ?????????...

yes! ... three of us saw a ufo this evening at dusk time, in littleton, right before the sun set in the west. ... it was as close as 100 yards away, flying right over the new littleton police station on route 119 (which runs east / west), near the brand new demoulas market basket supermarket plaza on route 119, near littleton center! ... 

my sister's boyfriend (who saw it first, and pointed it out, as he was standing in a westerly direction), myself, and my lifelong friend, were standing in my sister's driveway when her boyfriend said: "wow! ... look at that! ... what is that?!" ... my friend and i immediately looked up into the western / southwestern sky, and we all saw the exact same thing at the same time! ... it was a ufo !! ... 

it was flying no more than 100 feet, if that, over the tree lines on the southern side of route 119, heading west. ... the object was heading from the northeastern sky towards the southwestern sky just before sunset. the sun was shining on it from our left, in the southwest, as we looked due west. ... 

it came from out of nowhere! it made no sounds, at all. it was internally illuminated, colored a very bright white in the center. all around the perimeter of the object, it was surrounded by a fine bright metallic blue band of bright light. it was oval-shaped, but not perfectly oval-shaped from our vantage point. also, it was moving very fast !! it left no vapor trails or exhaust fumes behind it. it cast no shadow on the ground. it made no normal aviation type sounds that a jet, or an aeroplane, or a air liner, or a small propellor plane, or a weather helicopter, or a military chopper might make. nothing! no sounds! it zipped across the sky, coming from, virtually, out of nowhere! the whole perception of it, for all three of us, only lasted between two and three seconds, at the most, but that was enough to get a very good look at it. also, it appeared to be descending, as if it intended to land somewhere off to the southwest in a farm field in one of the western farms that run along both sides of route 119 on the west side of highways 495. ... 

it was right above the tree line! ... 

we all thought it was going to crash, and we were expecting to hear a loud bang, and possibly see flames and smoke. ... 

but just then, something really weird happened that none of us have ever seen before (and i have seen a ufo now, after this, for the third time in my life): instead of the bright, silent, wicked fast, descending, oval-shaped, and internally illuminated object crashing to the ground over and past the trees nearby the new, littleton police station, the object, amazingly, split apart into three separate flying round, white, oval lights with a blue tint around the perimeter, and in formation, these three objects all continued flying / zipping / floating / gliding / piercing west through the sky over the tree line by route 119, and then totally disappeared from our sight! ... 

gone! ... into thin air! ... 

did they land? ... did they crash? ... did they change direction on a dime? ... did they hover even closer to the ground? ... did they zip off to the south or to the north behind the trees and beyond our sight so fast that we could not see them change direction? ... or, did they zoom up and out of our lower atmosphere instantly and so fast that the human eye cannot detect the exit path of their motion?! ... 

we do not know! ... but, we do know this: we all saw it at the same time. we saw it appear from, apparently, out of nowhere. ... we saw it split into three separate ovals or spheres. ... lastly, we saw it then totally disappear beyond the tree line without a trace! ... it was real! ... did anyone else see that? ...

we all felt totally amazed by what we all had just seen!
content.summary: Bright white and blue-circled, oval-shaped ufo splits into three objects and disappears from sight!

content.detailedDescription:
On october 28, 2015, between 8 and 9-pm cdt, it was dark and i was returning from a 45-minute walk. 
i went through the lake highlands baptist church parking lot, at the intersection of northcliff drive and parkhurst drive. 
this church is about 1-mile northeast of white rock lake in northeast dallas, texas. 
directly to my southwest, about 20-degrees above the horizon, were about twelve orange lights, forming about six distinct pairs. 
the lights were each uniformly as bright as a full venus, but were pure orange in color. 
no faa aircraft navigation colors were visible, specifically white, red and green. 
the lights appeared to be over the fair park area, at about 5,000-feet in altitude and 5-miles distance. 
the span inside each pair was comparable to a 737, from wingtip to wingtip. 
each two lights appeared to be mated, but i could not see any solid object between the lights. 
none of the pairs seemed attached with a different pair, as they slowly moved around independently. 
each pair was separate of the other pairs and they appeared to be at various staggered distances. 
i only saw a flat-on view of these things from their northeast side, and do not know the other side. 
another witness 71975 saw the lights from another angle and could give triangulation. 
a jetliner was directly behind the lights to the southwest at about 10,000-feet altitude and 10-miles away.  
this aircraft apparently left d-fw airport and was traveling  in a southeast direction behind the lights. 
the night was clear and the lights were steady for 5-minutes, so they were not natural phenomena. 
they were much too large, bright, high and stable to be chinese lanterns. 
these were illegally hovering near a love field flight path, five miles south of the runway, for five minutes without proper navigation colors; therefore, they were not man-made objects. 
these orange lights should have been easily seen by love field aircraft and traffic control and recorded. 
the pairs each slowly faded out one by one after about five minutes.
content.summary: Orange light pairs, 8 to 9-pm cdt, 10-28-2015, seen from northcliff and parkhurst drive, dallas, texas.

content.detailedDescription:
My fiancé was taking out the garbage and asked me to come look at the very bright star.  when i saw it, i told her that it was a flare from ft. carson, but we should get her binoculars to observe it.  she did, but i went looking for my camera and cell phone to call for additional witnesses. when i came back out, she told me that she watched it go very fast in a ene direction, then turn toward the nw.  
when i looked, i thought it looked like an airplane flying toward the nw.  there was another airplane flying in a nne (normal flight path) direction.
when she described the movements and speed, i knew it was not a flare or an aircraft.  it was still in the sky traveling away from us at what appeared to be aircraft speed so i decided to call 911.
later, a policeman came out and interviewed us and we were able to point out the directions in the sky.

content.detailedDescription:
When outside with my daughter to walk the dog at about 6:15, we happened to be looking up at the constellations when my daughter noticed a upside down w shaped object coming towards us. this object was noticeable due to the rows of lights outlining the craft, forming an upside down w-shape. this object was about a football field across and 300 ft in the sky above flying from the northwest towards the southeast.  the craft’s lights were slightly dimmer than the stars in the sky, yet still very noticeable. the craft, though very low to the ground, was silent as it flew over our heads. as it passed over our heads, the left side of the object moved in towards itself, making the upside-down w shape fold in on itself, allowing it to turn more towards the southeast. after this it disappeared out of sight. 

we believed this to be the last of the sighting and turned to go inside to draw a picture of the craft at about 6:17 when we noticed more activity towards the northeast. this time the objects were on the horizon and they looked entirely different. at first i thought they were 5 intensely bright meteorites due to the burning tales which they emitted. but we noticed they were lined in a vertically slanted row and not moving, so they were definitely not meteorites. after about 5 seconds, they suddenly moved into a circle. one of the lights on the left moved more towards the west, while the other lights began to come together at the center of the circle, lowered beyond sight due to the trees and homes blocking the view, falling out of our sight. finally, the one light remaining towards the west followed the others beyond sight as well. the entire event lasted from about 6:15 pm at the first sighting to 6:20 pm mountain standard time in the area around bear creek lake park near the intersection of morrison road and south kipling parkway in lakewood, colorado.
content.summary: Inverted w shaped ufo flew over us, nw to se direction.  lights lining the craft.  then saw 5 bright lights on horizon in slanted vertical line, came together to form a circle , one off to side more, descended below tree line and could not see anymore.

content.detailedDescription:
Several years ago i reported my wife and i saw s strange event in the sky. it was more what we didn't see than what we did. the report described the following incident:
we were driving southbound on i-75 between tampa and bradenton, fl.
above us and to the right we observed two (2) jet planes that appeared to be flying in formation.
the odd thing that drew my attention was the vapor trail was getting longer behind only one of the planes. the other plane appeared to be pulling its vapor trail behind it.
it was only later i realized the best explanation for the event is we were watching one (1) airplane, being shadowed by a reflection of itself. the reflective surface had to be "shadowing" another plane; and was flying at the same speed. that's why the vapor trail that ended at the edge of the reflective surface appeared to be pulled behind the reflection of the plane.
i reported it here after i realized that was the case.
here's why i'm writing you now:
i still think about that event, and i just now realized that whatever reflective surface was shadowing that jet was probably doing it to prevent detection by radar.
there was an unseen object flying in the same airspace as another visible aircraft that would all appear as one blip on radar to air traffic control in the metro-tampa area.
i think this behavior, flying close to another craft, now seems like an attack strategy that was being utilized or tested. without knowing what the mission was i can't even guess if that object did anything after it was out of my sight.
who knows what might be flying over us if we can't see it or detect it with radar?
content.summary: Reflective object reported previously

content.detailedDescription: I was taking an evening walk around 7:15 pm and for some reason, i looked up at the sky. at the time, i was directly in front of my driveway, looking away from my home.  i saw four oval to rectangular-shaped objects in the sky that were moving counter-clockwise, coming together and then splitting apart. i had no idea what they were.  my son saw two more in another part of the sky. my husband and daughter also saw them. they were moving in a circle and then meeting up in the middle. this went on for about 2 hours, until they faded.  they were - at one point - very bright in the sky, and that day was partly cloudy. it even sprinkled around 8 pm. my daughter and i watched them until they faded away. i reported the same thing in may 2014. that first sighting occurred on a starry, clear night at around 11:30 pm.  my husband and daughter also saw them in may 2014.  i tried to take a picture and video both times, but nothing came through.  i was in awe to be honest. i wasn't afraid.  in fact, i'd love to see them again. i posted on another site over a week ago, and the post that followed mine included an event that mirrored my description (same type of sighting, same night, same time) and was in a town not too far from mine. i know we witnessed the same thing.
content.summary: 4 lights traveling counterclockwise, coming together and then moving apart

content.detailedDescription:
Me & my friends have witnessed several starlike objects appear out of nowhere  between 7:00 p.M. & 8:30 p.M for the past several weeks coming from the north part of the sky going south.The weather had gave us clear skies every night until here lately.As soon as the stars come out,these really bright objects will appear over us.They will brighten extremely bright & then pulsate & looks kinda like a strobe light before dimming back down barely seeing it or sometimes dimming completely out of sight.They don't seem to be moving fast & you can tell they are under the clouds.When ever they start getting bright,they also seem to slow down before speeding back up along it's path.
saw 2 starlike objects close togetherwatching us & appearing to hover blending in with other stars before vanishing before our eyes.

i took binoculars & zoomed right on them but,it was like looking directly into car headlights,no object seen. airplanes were really busy that night.These are no airplanes,planets or iss or anything else that we've saw all of our lives.If they are drones, they are not any type of drone the public can access or buy.These would have to be high tech drones that are either gov. or from out of this world.

on thursday night,around 8:00 p.M.,we was looking east & 2 stars appeared out of nowhere & was side by side fixed into the clear dark sky amongst many other stars.They were at eye level not high up at all. i thought this was strange & for a short moment i thought they were stars.I thought,they haven't been there the whole time though.We had all been outside since it had gotton dark.These 2 very bright star like objects appeared to be hovering or fixed but they could of actually been traveling toward us going west very slow.Anyway, within about 4 minutes of starring at them,they didn't appear to be getting closer & all of a sudden,they both vanished.
i figured they were still there somewhere,without being lit up.Like being sneaky & spying.

about 10 minutes later,i shouted,"hey where are you"?)"get bright for me,so we can see where your at" & all of a sudden at that moment, low in the northern part of the sky, a really bright starlike object appeared & started moving slow going north away from us. oh & i had the heavens above app on my phone so there wasn't any type of satellites during the events stated.No noise only silence. i wanted to share my story with everyone.I guess we'll be looking every night for these strange objects now.Although it is creepy.From the stories i read on this site,it sounds a lot like what others have reported.Whatever we are seeing,it's really bizzare & seems to watching & spying on us.
content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Straight-line path,Path then hovering
content.summary: Saw 2 starlike objects close togetherwatching us & appearing to hover blending in with other stars before vanishing before our eyes

content.detailedDescription:
We were trick-or-treating in our neighbourhood. we were crossing the street to go to another house when we noticed lights in the sky.

at first we thought it was a satellite, but then we realized that it wasn't on a set path. then we noticed it was getting higher and higher in the sky. we then thought it was an airplane, but then we noticed that it was going all over the place and that it was way too fast and way too big to be an airplane.

we stood and watched it. it had 3 square lights in a row. it also had a slight aura of white light around it. it went from the north-eastern horizon to the south-eastern horizon, on a crooked path, in about 2 minutes. it went all over the place and we could not predict its trajectory. then we trick-or-treated at the next house and it was gone.

neither of us were scared, but we were both extremely fascinated. we talked about what we saw, and then realized that there was no one else around to ask. we were the only ones on the street. 

we lost sight of it after we went to the next house.
content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Craft flying in random directions. very fast.

content.detailedDescription:
I went out on my 5th floor balcony to have a cigarette, and saw 2 red spheres flying in a strange pattern from the se to the nw. i thought they were planes.
while maintaining the same altitude, one would slow down while the other sped up. then the second one would slow down while the first one sped up. one orb was above the other by a distance of about ten times their diameter.
they seemed low in the sky, approx 500 ft to 3 thousand feet elevation, depending how far away they were.

it's possible they were zigzagging, because as they zigged in my direction, they  could give the appearance of slowing down, but actually just be a direction change toward me. one 'zigged' this way while the other 'zagged' that way a bit, their turns were at the exact same time, but out of sync, that is, turning in different directions at the exact same time.
it was as if they were flying in the same direction, but doing opposing zigzags as they followed their flight path, as in a search pattern.
they maintained the same distance from each other, one above the other.

the turns were quick and abrupt. the g-forces would have to be quite high during fast turns like that.

they moved from the sw to directly south of me, as they continued,
this pattern repeated itself 5 or six times until they moved out of sight behind my building.
i ran inside, grabbed my camera, and ran out the front of the building to get some video.
i didn't see the spheres again, but met two younger men who were quite excited as they told me they'd just seen all this fly overhead, and they said they saw them split up into six red flying balls.
they had both recorded the video on their i-phones.
i was really happy it was witnessed by others, and that they taped it.
i told them both to post their videos online.
content.summary: Saw 2 red glowing orbs dance with each other as they moved from se sky to nw

content.detailedDescription: August 2, 2015 - it was a warm clear sunday evening w light winds. my friend and i were sitting on the deck in my backyard. i live on a canal on padre island, so the deck is actually about 25 ft above the water on canal. all of a sudden my friend was startled by a bright light she noticed when she glanced to her left. when she noticed it, it caught my attention and we both jumped out of our seat in shock. there was a bright red/orange orb travelling in slow, straight path approx 100 ft above the water and travelling nw along the canal. we were in complete shock- could not speak and were scared to move. i had my phone in my hand, but it was so close to us as it was passing by us, i was scared to video it until it went past my house. the first thing my friend said was , " oh my gosh, is that a chinese lantern?" - at that time the object was about 2 houses down from mine and had not yet reached our location. as it got closer it was very obvious it was no chinese lantern or a drone of any type. first, it was too breezy for it to maintain straight flt path. also, as it got closer to us it made no noise at all, did not appear to have a specific structure or frame ( body). it was a large beachball size or slightly larger, bright sphere of red/orange light. the light was very bright and seemed to slightly pulsate never leave losing its vibrance but w no distinct pattern. as it passed my house i turned the video on my phone on and tried to videotape it as it flew steadily along the canal slowly ascending flying nw direction,  and all if a sudden it disappeared. the video and still shot i took is horrible in regard to clarity- i tried to zoom in and also include houses in video to show its proximity in sky to where we were. video did not capture the intense brightness. we have never seen anything like this ever! we are both very familiar w drone type crafts as they are getting more common these days- this was not a drone of any kind- it was startling, shocking, and slightly scary bc it was this bright large sphere of light. would def love to know what this was. now everytime we go outside at night we def pay more attention to what is in the sky. i have included video and two still photos taken that night, as well as two daytime pics to show area object was seen travelling.
content.summary: Warm clear night-my friend and i were sitting on my deck and all of a sudden a bright red/orange orb flew past us at a slow steady speed-no sound-slowly ascending then disappeared.

content.detailedDescription: I was at church, outdoor mass. i was watching vultures flying. a silver disc descended as from space at very high altitude above vultures. it then moved in a southerly direction for five seconds at a slow rate of speed and made a slight turn to the west. it then hovered for ten seconds after which it shot straight up and out of sight. it flew as if it was almost floating like a butterfly on the wind; very hard to describe. when i first saw it i new it was nothing that we have put in the air. i am a sky watcher and i have seen these silver discs four times in the last eight months. in day light they seem to reflect sun light. at night they are a bright white light. every time i see them they excite me and give me a strange feeling i have never had with any other event. i think it is because i am seeing something i know has not been made by man. it makes you think how little we know of the universe we live in.
content.flightPath: Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Clear sunny day silver disc appears as from space makes maneuver hovers then disappears straight up unusual flight seemed to float very high altitude.

content.detailedDescription: Smoking a cigarette in yard.  looked up and saw large orange light similar to a burning ember after a fireworks explosion, only much larger.  light traveled due north at a speed slower than the lights from a plane.  it seemed to not travel in a straight path but it didn't alter it's course.  i knocked on the window to get my wife's attention.  the light grew red and got smaller.  by the time my wife came outside (15-20 seconds) i had lost it in the trees.  i was sure at the time that it was a ufo.  when i came in the house my wife reminded me it was halloween and i started to suspect the sighting.  this morning i think that if it was a hoax it was very well done.  not that i am an expert.
content.summary: Large orange light in sky slowly traveling n.  increased speed, turned red, got smaller.  lost it in the trees.

content.detailedDescription: I was inside the house when my son called me to tell me that he could see it across state lines.  i tried to debunk it by looking for rays of light from a light show in a nearby shopping center but there weren't anything going on that evening.  the objects were in white color, circling in which at one point one of them change direction on a dime.  being intuitive allowed me to witness a lot of energy discharge in the air as well as being able to see energy discharge within in the clouds.  i felt as though i was in another world to be honest.  i came back in the house to review my video and it was like 3-5 minutes later i went outside to continue watching they were completely gone.  the clouds and the ufo's were gone.  there were no clouds in sight, the sky was crystal clear as it shows in my video but they did come back in which i didn't take a video of but i witnessed.  again, they were covered within the clouds that suddenly appeared.  also, being intuitive i can hear different frequencies and i have heard weird sound waves with what sounds like people mumbling.  i only hear this late a night.
content.summary: 3 white balls of energy swirling covered by a cloud
